# Cursor Rules for Panda Wiki Project

## Code Block Language Default
When generating documentation, if a code block doesn't specify a specific programming language, it should be marked as `text` by default. For example, use ```text instead of ```.

## Documentation Guidelines
- Use Chinese language for all documentation
- Keep explanations concise and clear
- Focus on practical examples and use cases
- Avoid overly complex technical details for beginner tutorials
- Emphasize conceptual understanding over code examples when appropriate

## File Organization
- Maintain clear directory structure
- Use descriptive file names
- Group related content in appropriate directories

## Code Examples
- When showing code examples, specify the language explicitly
- For configuration files, use appropriate language tags (xml, yaml, json, etc.)
- For shell commands, use ```bash
- For general text or explanations, use ```text 